.5, 503.3, 621.6, 519.7]}, {"text": "n 30 31 28 26 33 32 33", "bbox": [128.4, 525.0, 608.3, 537.5]}, {"text": "Reversal rs 0.397 -0.103 -0.032 -0.275 -0.099 0.088 -0.325 0.328", "bbox": [51.0, 541.0, 701.5, 556.3]}, {"text": "learning p 0.030 0.588 0.870 0.174 0.591 0.631 0.069 0.067", "bbox": [58.5, 556.7, 701.5, 573.1]}, {"text": "n 30 30 28 26 32 32 32 32", "bbox": [128.4, 578.4, 688.2, 590.9]}, {"text": "Note:", "bbox": [42.7, 595.4, 65.6, 606.5]}, {"text": "Reversal learning scores (i.e., the number of trials to reach the learning criterion in the reversal task) were multiplied by -1 in such a way that the subjects that were faster", "bbox": [57.8, 604.5, 730.0, 617.6]}, {"text": "to reverse had the highest scores.", "bbox": [57.8, 616.8, 191.9, 627.9]}, {"text": "Furthermore, the four ﬁrst principal components had positive and negative loading", "bbox": [235.9, 646.4, 701.0, 663.5]}, {"text": "values (Table 3), which reﬂects the fact that the different measures of plasticity were", "bbox": [235.9, 665.3, 706.5, 682.4]}, {"text": "not equivalent.", "bbox": [235.9, 686.0, 318.6, 701.2]}, {"text": "There were differences in the level of plasticity expressed by individuals depending", "bbox": [251.0, 704.9, 723.1, 720.1]}, {"text": "on the social gradient they were exposed to. Most notably, the magnitude of the", "bbox": [235.9, 723.7, 692.2, 739.0]}, {"text": "changes in behavioral responses was smaller when the ﬁsh were tested twice without an", "bbox": [235.9, 740.8, 729.9, 757.9]}, {"text": "audience compared to when they were observed two times by different audience", "bbox": [235.9, 761.5, 693.1, 776.8]}, {"text": "individuals or when we compared the average response with and without an audience", "bbox": [235.9, 780.3, 725.3, 795.6]}, {"text": "(Fig. 4). However, only the difference between gradient A and C was signiﬁcant for", "bbox": [235.9, 797.4, 710.5, 814.5]}, {"text": "measures of neophobia (t29 = -2.347, p = 0.026). Finally, for the three personality", "bbox": [235.9, 815.9, 701.4, 834.4]}, {"text": "traits measured, we found a signiﬁcant association between the amount of plasticity", "bbox": [235.9, 835.1, 713.0, 852.2]}, {"text": "exhibited and the value of the trait during the ﬁrst trial (Neophobia, A: rs = 0.644,", "bbox": [235.9, 853.9, 705.1, 872.2]}, {"text": "n = 30, p < 0.001; B: rs = 0.526, n = 26, p = 0.006; Exploration, A: rs = 0.561, n = 31,", "bbox": [235.9, 874.7, 718.8, 891.1]}, {"text": "p = 0.001; B: rs = 0.488, n = 33, p = 0.004 & Anxiety, A: rs = 0.481, n = 28, p = 0.010;", "bbox": [235.9, 893.6, 723.8, 910.0]}, {"text": "Gibelli et al. (2018), PeerJ, DOI 10.7717/peerj.5454 10/17", "bbox": [42.7, 944.5, 729.9, 957.7]}]}